  <prompt>
    Close ledger entry RB-T034-01 by repairing `AgentConfigurationService.GetExposedPlaybookIdsAsync` in
    `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Agent/AgentConfigurationService.cs` to honor the `CancellationToken` parameter.

    Production fix per ledger Recommended Fix section: add `cancellationToken.ThrowIfCancellationRequested();` as the FIRST statement
    inside `GetExposedPlaybookIdsAsync` (line ~47). Defensively apply the same to the 3 sibling public async methods
    (`IsCapabilityEnabledAsync`, `IsRolePermittedAsync`, `InvalidateCacheAsync`) since they share the gap — but the asserting test
    only exercises `GetExposedPlaybookIdsAsync`.

    Test impact: 1 Skip'd test (`AgentConfigurationServiceTests.GetExposedPlaybookIdsAsync_RespectsCancellationToken`) flips Skip -> Pass.
    Per NFR-04: commit message MUST cite "RB-T034-01" + resolution mode `repaired`.
  </prompt>

  <role>BFF production-fix engineer closing a LOW-severity real-bug ledger entry under repair-not-rewrite discipline.</role>

  <goal>
    `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Agent/AgentConfigurationService.cs` calls `cancellationToken.ThrowIfCancellationRequested()` at the top of
    `GetExposedPlaybookIdsAsync` (and the 3 sibling async public methods defensively). 1 Skip'd test in
    `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Api/Agent/AgentConfigurationServiceTests.cs` has its `Skip = "..."` removed and passes.
    Ledger entry RB-T034-01 row updated to `repaired`.
  </goal>

