  <context>
    <background>
      Per r1 ledger entry RB-T034-01 (filed 2026-05-31, fix-by 2026-07-31): the cancellation contract is unobserved in live traffic (M365 Copilot agent endpoint passes `CancellationToken.None`); the unit test surfaces the gap because `MemoryDistributedCache` (and Redis fast-path) does not raise `OperationCanceledException` synchronously on pre-cancelled tokens.

      Recommended production fix is a single-line addition; the defensive extension to 3 sibling methods is good-citizen even though no test asserts them today. RB-T070-01 covers the same anti-pattern in `AgentConversationService` (task 035) — applying the same fix discipline.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="029" status="must-be-complete">Phase 2 exit triple-run validation (zero failures) before Phase 3 starts</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

