    <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/real-bug-ledger.md</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Load r1 ledger entry RB-T034-01 (lines ~120-179 of `real-bug-ledger.md`) for the documented bug + recommended fix.</step>
    <step order="2">Read `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Agent/AgentConfigurationService.cs`. Locate `GetExposedPlaybookIdsAsync` (~line 44) and the 3 sibling methods (`IsCapabilityEnabledAsync`, `IsRolePermittedAsync`, `InvalidateCacheAsync`).</step>
    <step order="3">Add `cancellationToken.ThrowIfCancellationRequested();` as the FIRST statement of `GetExposedPlaybookIdsAsync`. Defensively add the same to the 3 sibling public async methods.</step>
    <step order="4">Build BFF: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`. Must succeed with zero new warnings.</step>
    <step order="5">Edit `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Api/Agent/AgentConfigurationServiceTests.cs`: remove `Skip = "..."` on `GetExposedPlaybookIdsAsync_RespectsCancellationToken` (~line 444); remove per-test `[Trait("status","real-bug-pending-fix")]` override.</step>
    <step order="6">Run targeted tests: `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --filter "FullyQualifiedName~AgentConfigurationServiceTests"`. Re-enabled test must pass.</step>
    <step order="7">Update `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/real-bug-ledger.md` RB-T034-01 row: status → `repaired`, add fix-commit SHA placeholder + today's date.</step>
    <step order="8">Commit: `fix(bff-api): honor CancellationToken in AgentConfigurationService (RB-T034-01; repaired)` — message cites ledger entry ID + resolution mode per NFR-04.</step>
    <step order="9">Update `projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/current-task.md` with completion + commit SHA.</step>
  </steps>

